<subSubSection id="2023331FEA457AAA2226A5923F266474" pageId="null" pageNumber="395" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="4434A44CEE1789ECE6B5BF830B891D0B" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Rostrote Kopfbinse</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="EF6CACACBC493D24B227F0E3705BAF84" pageId="null" pageNumber="395" type="description">
<paragraph id="C352A318D4A90D9ADCBECF44359A69CF" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">
10-40 cm hoch; dichte, feste Horste bildend. 
<normalizedToken id="506FE3FA740F042BDC13245C087180B4" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="4D627B7DF159B78283244A80FE40BA3C" originalValue="borstenförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">borstenfoermig</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis id="5B6109DA2816DFFDEC6A66D2AA59681A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">
<normalizedToken id="8F421A8F3520A9E94DDA2631D43973D6" originalValue="höchstens" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">hoechstens</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
⅓ 
<emphasis id="F18AA1B756A2930765C6802AFD62E6D7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">
so lang wie die Stengel. Unterstes Hochblatt meist braun, 
<normalizedToken id="4B1ED4D3B6378C8E46F7696BEF2CC89D" originalValue="kürzer" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">kuerzer</normalizedToken>
oder wenig 
<normalizedToken id="DF811EB541304F19097F4D797A2165B1" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">laenger</normalizedToken>
als der 
<normalizedToken id="28CD806A782D4A394D149DB069D1122E" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="44D64B384C7E5D9788FDC1C8712042EC" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
ca. 1 cm lang, schwarzbraun, aus 1-5 
<normalizedToken id="8612C22FB71E95D6DCD83C677C75689C" originalValue="Ähren" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Aehren</normalizedToken>
bestehend, die meist je 2-3 
<normalizedToken id="863DDBCBB2257BB274C3E48168695070" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Blueten</normalizedToken>
tragen. Perigonborsten 3-6, wenig 
<normalizedToken id="2BDF0EAEA2FA20069ABAAA7D94C4EE17" originalValue="kürzer" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">kuerzer</normalizedToken>
bis 
<normalizedToken id="4F20CE6F10C9F3A43E277E7C2CE55B29" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">laenger</normalizedToken>
als die reife Frucht, oft 
<normalizedToken id="0D872005B7D9A64511F9931F47F8884E" originalValue="früh" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">frueh</normalizedToken>
abfallend. Frucht wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="67AB774BA7DFBBED60C766B2348894B2" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Schoenus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="395" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigricans">
<emphasis id="76DEE1A5206D44875DC6B2A25C50009D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Sch. nigricans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 1). - 
<normalizedToken id="644F5BC24C05259A08A99F922E5CF83F" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="4E5512FCCF84B25EB1A0628866DFC3FC" originalValue="Später" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Spaeter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="73B13CE960E9E289CA17B5F9DD5303D3" originalValue="Frühling" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Fruehling</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="500C21FD3D9C54A4F5EB77B0BAB1BBAE" originalValue="früher" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">frueher</normalizedToken>
Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D011F26965CE6CB8402B12D69AF95EAC" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis id="66C9FE91F78D4CA9EDB043A2A63EF7B9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">
<pageBreakToken id="9929F6BEE19E1792A70A30661EF34604" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Zytologische</pageBreakToken>
Angaben. 2n
</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="87F9E7EB6B47EDE69A9DCA073C392425" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">76:</emphasis>
Material aus Schweden (
<normalizedToken id="1B7CC5D8BB915444C6E1E41D6854D90A" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Loeve</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="B78F74BA9FA7432DD4307B3D24A901F3" originalValue="Löve" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Loeve</normalizedToken>
1944b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA146F2B4D6BF212C4862E2FE5C69D20" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis id="18E8574BC4588C69471D051633655CE6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin und montan, selten subalpin. Standort sehr 
<normalizedToken id="6FC0FC18BC4963B9ACD83FC03983D364" originalValue="ähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">aehnlich</normalizedToken>
jenem von 
<taxonomicName id="319C9E83C6CDDDD851DD0AB6C0D13704" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Schoenus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="395" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigricans">
<emphasis id="5CBB8BBE650652C5CFCEA8B3362F7876" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Sch. nigricans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 1); der Boden ist jedoch weniger kalkhaltig, Tuffbildung fehlt, Torf ist oft vorhanden. Vor allem im 
<emphasis id="C33D74C5595349CE7381D49B020022E6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Schoenetum schoenetosum ferruginei</emphasis>
W. Koch 1926; diese Subassoziation leitet vom 
<emphasis id="95CE4530693509FE403BDE23F1730787" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Schoenetum nigricantis</emphasis>
W. Koch 1926 zum 
<emphasis id="E11A9DB719323DFA41AB49BFDD1D05C3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Molinietum coeruleae</emphasis>
W. Koch 1926 
<normalizedToken id="49E1810DA9A97FC90D488A7C097B59A5" originalValue="über" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">ueber</normalizedToken>
. In der montanen und subalpinen Stufe tritt 
<taxonomicName id="26E333EEC0DDFD2F1AC1C2E9F734BA44" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Schoenus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="395" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferrugineus">
<emphasis id="1303CB81BB9809960A9F58367A423A54" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Sch. ferrugineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
oft an die Stelle von 
<emphasis id="3551677D93425EB20954891BF8444D19" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">
<taxonomicName id="C7E69FA0A54B01503C4B283E9FB28A65" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Schoenus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="395" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigricans">Sch. nigricans</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Weitere Angaben von Koch (1926) und Zobrist (1935).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D9B73E696D283C0C8DBC102642ACCC57" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis id="E2CEFD2F6F6AE5D03B4FE4F5419A0A12" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">
Verbreitung. 
<normalizedToken id="858F97FD299B366042E23E659AE7E293" originalValue="Europäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Europaeische</normalizedToken>
Pflanze:
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="C2F539CCD7D8BF5527E962DEC676235F" originalValue="Westwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">Westwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis ins Rheinland, 
<normalizedToken id="FAF4F4094678BC43934752927CA5B6C4" originalValue="nordwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">nordwaerts</normalizedToken>
in Skandinavien bis 67° NB, isoliert in Schottland; 
<normalizedToken id="4D61AE7CB31DD0FDFE95FFEBEA0B4DC0" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis in die Alpen und Balkanhalbinsel, 
<normalizedToken id="5315BEFFF603791BF33738CE1A2BC9EF" originalValue="ostwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">ostwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis in die Ukraine (Dongebiet). Verbreitungskarte von Meusel (1964). - Im Gebiet verbreitet, ziemlich 
<normalizedToken id="B22F229BC971E04964B6F27094DAE3FE" originalValue="häufig" pageId="null" pageNumber="395">haeufig</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
